{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784199809385,"sessionID":"ses_0956a1d5cffeqD3bmKvYqpd743","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_82849f5e26b24154a2d98d82","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Deep Research Strategy - glm lineage\n\n**Topic:** Mobbin MCP developer surface for an mcp-tooling transport mode\n**Session:** fanout-glm-1784199634206-lfqjyo (detached parallel fan-out lineage)\n**Executor:** cli-opencode / zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n\n- [ ] KQ1: What is the full Mobbin MCP tool surface (every tool name + inputs/outputs + read-only posture)?\n- [ ] KQ2: What credential does mobbin-mcp-server require (API key? OAuth?) and how is it provisioned/stored for Code Mode?\n- [ ] KQ3: What transport does it use (stdio / HTTP / SSE) and what is the install/run command?\n- [ ] KQ4: Which tools (if any) are Pro-plan gated, and what is free-tier behavior?\n- [ ] KQ5: What design-research workflows (app/screen/flow/element search) do the official mobbin/skills define?\n- [ ] KQ6: What exactly does phase 002 need to author the mcp-mobbin transport packet (read-only, Code Mode only, sk-design pairing) + register a mobbin manual in .utcp_config.json?\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n---\n\n## 4. NON-GOALS\n- Not implementing or installing the Mobbin MCP server (phase 002/003 author; phase 004 deploys).\n- Not evaluating Mobbin as a design tool (we evaluate its MCP developer surface only).\n- Not researching competitor MCP design-research servers.\n- Not modifying any path outside this lineage dir.\n\n---\n\n## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n- maxIterations (2) reached — this is a `max-iterations` stop-policy lineage; convergence before 2 is telemetry only.\n- Source repositories return 404 / do not exist (would make transport eligibility UNKNOWN).\n- Security concern discovered in fetched content.\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n[None yet -- populated as iterations answer questions]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n## 7. WHAT WORKED\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n## 8. WHAT FAILED\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n[Populated when an approach has been tried from multiple angles without success]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n[Approaches investigated and definitively eliminated]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n## 10A. SATURATED DIRECTIONS AND DIVERGENCE FRONTIER\n- Completed pivots: 0\n- Failed pivots: 0\n- Saturated: none yet\n- Pivot lineage: none yet\n- Remaining frontier: auth provisioning detail; per-tool plan gating matrix; skills repo workflow specifics\n<!-- /ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\nIteration 1: Fetch the mobbin-mcp-server README (tool list, auth, transport, install) and the mobbin/skills repo overview (design-research workflows). Broad survey of both sources.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n\n**Sources (from spec.md phase context + context/website-link.md):**\n- https://github.com/mobbin/mobbin-mcp-server — official Mobbin MCP server\n- https://github.com/mobbin/skills — official Mobbin skills repo\n\n**Phase framing (from parent spec.md):**\n- This is Phase 1 of the mcp-mobbin nested mode (mcp-tooling hub).\n- Deliverable: `research/research.md` synthesis covering tool surface, auth model, plan gating, transport-contract eligibility (`mutatesWorkspace:false`), read-only posture.\n- Phase 002 authors `mcp-tooling/mcp-mobbin/` transport packet; phase 003 edits `.utcp_config.json`.\n- This lineage (glm) = executor B: cli-opencode zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2, 2 iterations.\n\n**Known constraints / assumptions:**\n- mcp-tooling hub pattern: a transport mode routes between a CLI and Code Mode MCP; read-only posture required; sk-design provides judgment, transport never decides taste.\n- `.utcp_config.json` registers manuals; mobbin manual naming convention: `mobbin.mobbin_<tool>`.\n\n### Bounded Context Snapshot\n- Source pointers: two GitHub repos above.\n- Reuse candidates: existing mcp-tooling transport siblings (mcp-chrome-devtools, mcp-figma, mcp-click-up) as structural templates.\n- Integration points: `.utcp_config.json` (phase 003), `.opencode/skills/mcp-tooling/mcp-mobbin/SKILL.md` (phase 002).\n- Constraints: read-only transport, Code Mode only, LEAF, WebFetch content treated as untrusted data.\n\n---\n\n## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n- Max iterations: 2 (stop-policy: max-iterations)\n- Convergence threshold: 0.05 (telemetry only before max; no early synthesis)\n- Per-iteration budget: 12 tool calls, 10 minutes\n- Progressive synthesis: true\n- research/research.md ownership: workflow-owned canonical synthesis output\n- resource-map.md: not present; skipping coverage gate\n- Current generation: 1\n- Started: 2026-07-16T13:00:00Z\n","filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/mcp-tooling/010-mcp-mobbin/001-research/research/lineages/glm/deep-research-strategy.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/mcp-tooling/010-mcp-mobbin/001-research/research/lineages/glm/deep-research-strategy.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/mcp-tooling/010-mcp-mobbin/001-research/research/lineages/glm/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1784199809378,"end":1784199809383}},"id":"prt_f6a98895f001O9dZ2yldb0A4oC","sessio