{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784199952973,"sessionID":"ses_0956a1d5cffeqD3bmKvYqpd743","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_5817aeb78d66483cb346a8a7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Deep Research Strategy - glm lineage\n\n**Topic:** Mobbin MCP developer surface for an mcp-tooling transport mode\n**Session:** fanout-glm-1784199634206-lfqjyo (detached parallel fan-out lineage)\n**Executor:** cli-opencode / zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n\n- [ ] KQ1: What is the full Mobbin MCP tool surface (every tool name + inputs/outputs + read-only posture)? — **PARTIAL: transport + workflow known; exact tool names pending**\n- [ ] KQ2: What credential does mobbin-mcp-server require (API key? OAuth?) and how is it provisioned/stored for Code Mode? — **OPEN (deferred to iteration 2)**\n- [x] KQ3: What transport does it use (stdio / HTTP / SSE) and what is the install/run command? — **ANSWERED (partial): remote Streamable HTTP, `https://api.mobbin.com/mcp`, no local process; install detail pending**\n- [ ] KQ4: Which tools (if any) are Pro-plan gated, and what is free-tier behavior? — **OPEN (deferred to iteration 2)**\n- [x] KQ5: What design-research workflows (app/screen/flow/element search) do the official mobbin/skills define? — **ANSWERED (overview): single `mobbin-search` skill; exact SKILL.md tool calls pending**\n- [ ] KQ6: What exactly does phase 002 need to author the mcp-mobbin transport packet + register a mobbin manual in .utcp_config.json? — **PARTIAL: remote-URL transport shape known; manual fields pending**\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n---\n\n## 4. NON-GOALS\n- Not implementing or installing the Mobbin MCP server (phase 002/003 author; phase 004 deploys).\n- Not evaluating Mobbin as a design tool (we evaluate its MCP developer surface only).\n- Not researching competitor MCP design-research servers.\n- Not modifying any path outside this lineage dir.\n\n---\n\n## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n- maxIterations (2) reached — this is a `max-iterations` stop-policy lineage; convergence before 2 is telemetry only.\n- Source repositories return 404 / do not exist (would make transport eligibility UNKNOWN).\n- Security concern discovered in fetched content.\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n- **KQ3** (iter 1): Remote **Streamable HTTP** transport at `https://api.mobbin.com/mcp`; no local stdio process, no `command`/`args`. Client config is url-only. [SOURCE: github.com/mobbin/skills prerequisites]\n- **KQ5** (iter 1): One official skill, `mobbin-search` — searches Mobbin's screenshot library via MCP (images inline), visually inspects results, responds or builds an HTML evidence board. [SOURCE: github.com/mobbin/skills]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n## 7. WHAT WORKED\n- Reading both repo READMEs in one pass: decisively established the transport model and revealed the server repo is metadata-only (README + mcp.json + server.json + rules) (iteration 1).\n- Treating WebFetch output as untrusted data: no directive-like content encountered (iteration 1).\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n## 8. WHAT FAILED\n- Assuming the server repo README carries auth/plan-gating/tool-list: it does not. These live in docs.mobbin.com/mcp + server.json (iteration 1).\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n[None yet — single iteration]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n- \"Read auth/plan-gating/tool-list from the server repo README\": ruled out — READMEs omit them (iteration 1, evidence: github.com/mobbin/mobbin-mcp-server).\n- \"Local stdio process install (npx/node command)\": ruled out for this server — it is remote Streamable HTTP, url-only config (iteration 1).\n<!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n## 10A. SATURATED DIRECTIONS AND DIVERGENCE FRONTIER\n- Completed pivots: 0\n- Failed pivots: 0\n- Saturated: none yet\n- Pivot lineage: none yet\n- Remaining frontier: auth/API-key model; free-vs-Pro plan gating matrix; exact tool names from server.json + mobbin-search SKILL.md; .utcp_config.json manual field shape for a remote-URL MCP\n<!-- /ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n- Does `api.mobbin.com/mcp` require an API key / OAuth bearer, and how is the header passed in a Code Mode manual? (from iter 1 reflection)\n- Is the image-inline return path usable through Code Mode's call_tool_chain, or does it need a sk-design side-channel? (from iter 1 reflection)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\nIteration 2: (1) Resolve auth/API-key model + free-vs-Pro plan gating via `docs.mobbin.com/mcp` and `mobbin.com/mcp`; (2) capture exact tool surface from the repo `server.json`/`mcp.json` and the `mobbin/skills mobbin-search SKILL.md`; (3) derive the `.utcp_config.json` mobbin manual field shape for a remote-URL MCP and the read-only transport-packet contract. Broaden review angles rather than converge early.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n\n**Sources (from spec.md phase context + context/website-link.md):**\n- https://github.com/mobbin/mobbin-mcp-server — official Mobbin MCP server (metadata repo)\n- https://github.com/mobbin/skills — official Mobbin skills repo\n- https://docs.mobbin.com/mcp — setup/usage docs (auth + gating)\n- https://mobbin.com/mcp — product overview\n\n**Phase framing (from parent spec.md):**\n- Phase 1 of the mcp-mobbin nested mode (mcp-tooling hub).\n- Deliverable: `research/research.md` synthesis covering tool surface, auth model, plan gating, transport-contract eligibility (`mutatesWorkspace:false`), read-only posture.\n- Phase 002 authors `mcp-tooling/mcp-mobbin/` transport packet; phase 003 edits `.utcp_config.json`.\n- This lineage (glm) = executor B: cli-opencode zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2, 2 iterations.\n\n### Bounded Context Snapshot\n- Source pointers: four URLs above.\n- Reuse candidates: existing mcp-tooling transport siblings (mcp-chrome-devtools, mcp-figma, mcp-click-up) as structural templates.\n- Integration points: `.utcp_config.json` (phase 003), `.opencode/skills/mcp-tooling/mcp-mobbin/SKILL.md` (phase 002).\n- Constraints: read-only transport, Code Mode only, LEAF, WebFetch content treated as untrusted data.\n\n**resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.**\n\n---\n\n## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n- Max iterations: 2 (stop-policy: max-iterations)\n- Convergence threshold: 0.05 (telemetry only before max; no early synthesis)\n- Per-iteration budget: 12 tool calls, 10 minutes\n- Progressive synthesis: true\n- research/research.md ownership: workflow-owned canonical synthesis output\n- Current generation: 1\n- Started: 2026-07-16T13:00:00Z\n","filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/mcp-tooling/010-mcp-mobbin/001-research/research/lineages/glm/deep-research-strategy.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/mcp-tooling/010-mcp-mobbin/001-research/research/lineages/glm/deep-research-strategy.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/mcp-tooling/010-mcp-mobbin/001-research/research/lineages/glm/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1784199952963,"end":1784199952971}},"id":"prt_f6a9aba40001it1ZBahAk8EP1r","sessionID":"ses_0956a1d5cffeqD3bmKvYqpd743","messageID":"msg_f6a9a3f11001NmeqqsvjOQN0TJ"}}
